goods.DEF: tangible or intangible thing, except a service, that satisfies human wants and provides utility

EU financing.DEF: EU expenditures for the implementation of the EU policies.

excise duty.DEF: Indirect tax imposed by the government on a product, principally those such as tobacco, petrol and alcoholic drinks.

goodwill.DEF: An intangible asset taken into account in assessing the value of an enterprise and reflecting its reputation and customer loyalty.

working capital.DEF: The excess of current assets over current liabilities, representing the funds available for financing business activities.

in-service training.DEF: Training paid for and given during active work periods.

vocational training.DEF: Activities which aim at providing the skills, knowledge and aptitudes required for employment in a particular occupation (or a group of related occupations) in any field of economic activity.

overheads.DEF: Expenses incurred by a business other than direct manufacturing costs.

franchising.DEF: System whereby a company grants independent operators the right to market products or provide services using the franchiser's name and trademarks.

exemption from customs duties.DEF: The non-collection of duties under the Common Customs Tariff in the case of goods imported for personal use or by private individuals.

tax evasion.DEF: Reduction or minimisation of tax liability by unlawful means.

conglomerate.DEF: A large corporation or group of companies, built up through mergers and takeovers, which has interests in a wide range of business activities.

credit guarantee.DEF: Arrangement insuring a creditor against default by a debtor.

Council of the European Union.DEF: intergovernmental institution of the European Union representing the governments of the Member States at ministerial level, which drafts and adopts EU laws (along with the European Parliament), performs budgetary functions and coordinates policies

set-aside.DEF: Incentive to non-cultivation of land so as to limit agricultural production.

geochemistry.DEF: The chemistry of the earth's crust.

economic geography.DEF: The study of the geographical distribution of economic resources and their use.

board of directors.DEF: Primary decision-making body of a company elected by the shareholders.

political geography.DEF: Study of the distribution of political phenomena in geographical space.

geophysics.DEF: The study of the earth's physical properties and of the physical processes acting upon, above, and within the earth.

gerontology.DEF: The study of the social, psychological and biological aspects of ageing.

large business.DEF: Used for enterprises with 250 or more persons employed.

interest group.DEF: Group capable of exercising pressure on a decision taken at government level.

buying group.DEF: A group of companies set up to obtain more favourable conditions from suppliers than would be possible if each acted individually.

producer organisation.DEF: legally-constituted group of farmers and growers that assists in the distribution and marketing of products

trust in governement.DEF: confidence of citizens in the actions of a government to do what is right and perceived fair

holding company.DEF: A company which exists for the primary or sole purpose of holding controlling interests in other companies.

approval.DEF: Acknowledgement by an official authority of the quality of a product or service and of its conformity to standards.

food hygiene.DEF: Conditions and measures necessary to ensure the safety of food from production to consumption.

European Council.DEF: institution of the European Union that defines the general political directions and priorities of the Union but does not exercise legislative functions, consisting of the heads of state or government of the member states together with its President and the President of the Commission

AETR agreement.DEF: European agreement relating to the work of vehicle crews involved in international transport by road.

imperialism.DEF: The political, economic or cultural domination of one nation by another.

Community tax.DEF: Internal tax to which the staff of the European civil service are subject.

tax on consumption.DEF: Tax on purchases of goods and services.

tax on income.DEF: Tax owed by physical persons on their total income, calculated by adding earned income and investment income.

tax on employment income.DEF: Paid by the employer as a proportion of the wages paid.

incapacity for work.DEF: Disability due to an occupational accident or disease.

incompatibility.DEF: The holder of an elective office is forbidden to hold another office considered detrimental to the former.

incoterms.DEF: Uniform trade terms formulated by the International Chamber of Commerce.

indemnification.DEF: payment or reparations made for harm or loss

installation allowance.DEF: Grant for young farmers who are setting up a farm for the first time.

divergence indicator.DEF: Measure of the extent to which a currency in the EMS deviates from its central rate against the ECU.

price index.DEF: Instrument for measuring the movement of prices.

allocation of resources.DEF: In economics, assignment of available resources to various uses. In the context of an entire economy, resources can be allocated by various means, such as markets or central planning.

pharmaceutical industry.DEF: Consists of development, production, distribution and marketing of drugs and medications.

innovation.DEF: action or process of making changes in something established, especially by introducing new methods, ideas, or products, and by extension, the new method, idea, or product itself

final consumption.DEF: Final consumption represents the value of the goods and services used for the direct satisfaction of human needs.

EU financial instrument.DEF: European Union measures of financial support provided on a complementary basis from the budget in order to address one or more specific policy objectives of the Union. Such instruments may take the form of equity or quasi-equity investments, loans or guarantees, or other risk-sharing instruments, and may, where appropriate, be combined with grants.

economic integration.DEF: All procedures taken by two or more nations to create a common economic area.

agreement (EU).DEF: Agreements concluded by the European Union with non-member countries or international organisations within their areas of responsibility.

isolationism.DEF: The political principle or practice of a country not to participate in international affairs.

fallow.DEF: Of land left unseeded after being ploughed and harrowed to regain fertility for a crop.

academic writing.DEF: non-fiction writing that is produced as part of academic work in accordance with the standards of a particular academic subject or discipline

soil conditioning.DEF: Incorporation of substances into the soil to improve its physical and chemical properties.

legislative period.DEF: Period during which a legislative assembly exercises power.

tariff quota.DEF: Limit set on the quantity of goods which may be imported at a reduced or zero rate of duty.

free movement of workers.DEF: A fundamental aspect of the free movement of persons within the European Union. This concept implies the abolition of discrimination based on nationality as regards employment, wages and other working conditions, as well as the right to social, economic and cultural integration of the migrant worker and his/her family in the host State.

free circulation.DEF: System under which goods produced outside the European Union circulate freely within its territory after payment of customs duties when they are first imported into a Member State.

work contract.DEF: Contract between an employer and an individual employee.

industrial counterfeiting.DEF: To be used in combination with the product or the sector affected by the counterfeiting.

money-market liquidity.DEF: Means of payment readily available without the need to move funds.

electoral register.DEF: Register of persons who have the right to vote.

redemption of public debt.DEF: Repaying of a debt at a fixed rate or by annual instalments.

lockout.DEF: Closure of a factory by an employer in order to force workers to accept certain working conditions.

outline law.DEF: Law outlining general principles but allowing the government to use its parliamentary power to develop them further.

administrative check.DEF: formalised and automated check carried out  on all applications in order to verify eligibility and detect any irregularities

macroeconomics.DEF: The branch of economics concerned with aggregates, such as national income, consumption, and investment.

cyber resilience.DEF: capability of information systems and networks to withstand and recover from deliberate attacks, accidents, or naturally occurring threats or incidents

budgetary control.DEF: process of preparing budgets for the future period, comparing the standards set by the budget with the actual performance, looking out the reasons for the differences in performance, and taking corrective actions.

management audit.DEF: Systematic evaluation of management methods by teams from either within or outside the organisation.

absolute majority.DEF: Obtaining more than half the votes cast.

qualified majority.DEF: This requires more difficult conditions to be met than with an absolute majority, for example a two-thirds majority.

right to property.DEF: fundamental right to own property as enshrined in the Universal Declaration of Human Rights

power of attorney.DEF: The legal authority to act for another person in certain specified matters or the document conferring such authority.

futures market.DEF: Market in contracts to buy or sell goods or securities at a future date at a price agreed when the contract is made.

production control.DEF: quality control inspection applied to manufactured products

spot market.DEF: Market in which goods are sold for immediate delivery.

common market.DEF: A market common to two or more states.

EU market.DEF: Supply and demand of goods and services inside and the EU Member States.

supplies contract.DEF: Public contract having as their object the purchase, lease, rental, with or without option to buy, of products.

negotiated contract.DEF: Contract awarded at the discretion of an administrative body after a preliminary competition among potential contractors.

works contract.DEF: Having as its object either the execution the design or the execution of works related to construction of building

foreign exchange market.DEF: The place where national and foreign currencies are traded.

quality control of industrial products.DEF: Examination of industrial products at various stages of manufacture so as to ensure conformity to standards.

financial market.DEF: The place where transferable securities, mostly shares and bonds, are issued and traded.

money market.DEF: A market in short-term financial claims, e.g. bills of exchange, Treasury bills, interbank money and discount house deposits.

public contract.DEF: Contract binding a public body and a third party with a view to supplying work or services.

fluctuation margin.DEF: The band within which the value of a currency may fluctuate on either side of the central rate.

money supply.DEF: All means of payment which can be used in a given country.

raw material.DEF: natural, unprocessed materials or resources used in a production process, which are at a low level of completion compared to the final product or cost unit and which are converted by a manufacturer into a final product

radioactive materials.DEF: Nuclear material refers to the metals uranium, plutonium, and thorium, in any form, according to the IAEA.

support mechanism.DEF: Financial assistance mechanisms that support EU Member States in financial difficulties.

mediator.DEF: Intervention by a third party to resolve a conflict which could not be settled by normal administrative procedure.

household.DEF: A unit for the population census, every individual or group of individuals residing in the same dwelling.

paralympic games.DEF: major international sports competition for athletes with disabilities

measure having equivalent effect.DEF: Having an effect equivalent to that of customs duties or quantitative import restrictions.

share farming.DEF: Arrangement under which the landowner lets his land in return for part of the produce.

meteorology.DEF: The study of the earth's atmosphere, especially of weather-forming processes and weather forecasting.

microeconomics.DEF: The branch of economics concerned with particular commodities, firms, or individuals and the economic relationships between them.

plant health control.DEF: examination and, in some cases, analysis of samples to check that the plants or plant products are free from pests and meet specific requirements

return migration.DEF: Return of a migrant to his/her birthplace or last place of residence.

forced migration.DEF: A migratory movement in which an element of coercion exists, including threats to life and livelihood, whether arising from natural or man-made causes (e.g. movements of refugees and internally displaced persons as well as people displaced by natural or environmental disasters, chemical or nuclear disasters, famine, or development projects).

health control.DEF: examination or assessment carried out by health authorities or designated officials to ensure that public health standards, regulations and practices are maintained and respected in various environments

rural migration.DEF: migration of people from rural areas to urban areas

seasonal migration.DEF: Short-term, repetitive or cyclical movement of people from one geographical location to another for the purpose of improving the economic position of their household.

CIV Convention.DEF: International convention regarding the transportation of travellers and luggage by rail.

collective agreement.DEF: A written agreement on working conditions drawn up between one or more workers' organisations on the one side and one or more employers' organisations on the other.

social mobility.DEF: The movement of an individual or group from one social class or status to another.

reserve currency.DEF: Currency which countries are willing to hold as part of their foreign-exchange reserves.

monetary compensatory amount.DEF: Charge on imports or exports of agricultural products introduced to offset the difference between actual exchange rates and "green" rates and thus prevent distortions of competition.

motion of censure.DEF: Expression of disapproval or criticism addressed to the government by a parliamentary assembly.

complementarity agreement.DEF: Refers to industrial production in certain sectors where countries are jointly developing a programme of economic integration.

medium-sized business.DEF: Used for enterprises with 50-249 persons employed.

nationality.DEF: legal bond between a person and a state which does not indicate the person's ethnic origin

collective bargaining.DEF: Process in which representatives of employers and employees negotiate with a view to establishing a collective agreement.

neutrality.DEF: The state of a nation which voluntarily refuses to become involved in an international conflict.

standard of living.DEF: A level of subsistence or material welfare of a community, class, or person.

tariff nomenclature.DEF: classification established under the legislation of a contracting party for the purposes of levying duties of customs on imported goods

non-alignment.DEF: Refusal by a nation to align itself to one or other of the major powers.

non-attached member.DEF: Parliamentarian who does not belong to any political group.

labour standard.DEF: Standards concerning employment and working conditions, which are set out in collective agreements or laid down under labour law and labour regulations.

maintenance obligation.DEF: Obligation to provide financial support for a parent or relative.

climate security.DEF: impacts of the climate crisis on peace and security, particularly in fragile and conflict-affected settings

oligopoly.DEF: Situation in which a market is effectively controlled by a limited number of sellers.

oligopsony.DEF: Situation in which a market is effectively controlled by a limited number of buyers.

EU body.DEF: Established by the Treaties to exist alongside the institutions of the European Union.

judicial cooperation.DEF: Cooperation between the judicial bodies of different States, which may take the form of mutual assistance or the recognition and enforcement of judgments.

protest.DEF: act or statement registering objection, either expressed individually or organised collectively

cross voting.DEF: The voter makes up his own list by choosing candidates from several lists.

direct applicability.DEF: Applies to certain EU acts and means that they do not first need to be transposed into national law.

national park.DEF: An area of countryside for public use designated by a national government as being of notable scenic, environmental, scientific or historical importance.

political participation.DEF: participation of a person in the political process by making their opinions and beliefs known, most commonly through voting, protesting, public consultations

pauperisation.DEF: The gradual impoverishment of the population of a region or of a social class as the result of major changes in the economy of a region or country.

scale-up company.DEF: enterprise which has made the transition from start-up to growth stage

apprenticeship.DEF: A period of long-term training substantially carried out within an undertaking and regulated by statutory law or custom according to a contract which imposes mutual obligations on the trainee and the employer.

member country.DEF: Member of an international organisation other than the European Union.

financial equalisation.DEF: A systematic process of financial transfers directed towards the equalisation of the budget capacity or economic performance of different levels of federal governments.

inward processing.DEF: Processing of imported goods on which no duty is paid provided the finished product is re-exported.

outward processing.DEF: Temporary export of goods for further processing or repair under special customs arrangements.

carer.DEF: someone who takes care of a person who is young, old, ill or disabled, either as a family member or friend, or as a job

fishing permit.DEF: Authorisation to engage in fishing granted on payment of a fee.

business-to-business.DEF: transfers of products and services which occur between companies

small business.DEF: Used for enterprises with 1-49 persons employed.

arbitrage.DEF: Dealing in commodities, currencies or securities in two or more markets so as to take advantage of any differences in the prices quoted.

fuel cell.DEF: A device which directly converts chemical energy into electric energy from a controlled oxidation reaction between an electrolyte and a fuel, usually hydrogen or hydrocarbon.

financial planning.DEF: The activity of making decisions about how a public organisation should manage their financial arrangements.

plantation.DEF: An area of land planted with crops, usually on a large scale.

plasticiser.DEF: Product used to alter the mechanical and thermal properties of certain solid substances in order to increase their flexibility, lower their breaking temperature and render them easier to shape.

continental shelf.DEF: Irregular submarine margin of a continent over which territory the coastal State has sovereign rights to extract resources.

full employment.DEF: Characteristic of a country or region where all job-seekers are provided with work.

common agricultural policy.DEF: Concept referring to the set of legislation and practices adopted by the European Union to provide a common, unified policy on agriculture.

common commercial policy.DEF: European Union policy by which the European Union seeks to contribute to the progressive abolition of restrictions on international trade.

austerity policy.DEF: Cost control: reducing public spending, controlling incomes and prices.

intervention policy.DEF: Intervention of the State in certain economic or social matters.

pollution from land-based sources.DEF: Marine pollution caused by waste from the land or from inland waterways.

mixed cropping.DEF: The simultaneous growing of various crops in different areas of the same farm.

working population.DEF: All persons already gainfully employed or who declare themselves to be seeking employment.

persons in work.DEF: All persons in active employment, discounting the unemployed.

International Court of Justice.DEF: As the principal judicial organ of the UN, the International Court of Justice settles, in accordance with international law, legal disputes between States which have been submitted by the States themselves and gives advisory opinions on legal questions referred to it by authorised United Nations organs and specialised agencies.

pre-packaging.DEF: Wrapping of a product, in the absence of the purchaser, in such a way that the amount of product has a fixed value in volume or mass which is chosen in advance.

generalised preferences.DEF: Preferential customs arrangements which the industrialised countries, including the European Union, apply to developing countries.

agricultural levy.DEF: Variable charge levied at the external frontier of the EU on imports of agricultural products from third countries in order to offset the difference between world prices and the price levels agreed for the EU.

ECSC levy.DEF: Tax levied by the ECSC, since 1 January 1953, on the production of coal and steel in the community.

primacy of EU law.DEF: EU law takes precedence over any provision of the law of Member States which is contrary to it.

polluter pays principle.DEF: The principle by which costs of anti-pollution measures are chargeable to the party responsible for the pollution.

farm prices.DEF: Prices fixed within the framework of the Common Agricultural Policy.

cif price.DEF: Includes, in addition to the price of the goods themselves, the cost of transport and insurance to the port of destination.

hygiene product.DEF: goods, merchandise or product necessary for the personal health, safety and cleanliness of an individual

administrative order.DEF: An enforceable decision made by an authority belonging to the administrative hierarchy.

free-on-board price.DEF: The sales price of the goods and all expenses incurred up to the point of loading on board ship.

disciplinary proceedings.DEF: Procedure put in place by administrative or judicial authorities, or by a company, to deal with disciplinary violations or breaches of professional standards.

cost of living.DEF: The basic cost of the food, clothing, shelter, and fuel necessary to maintain life.

gross domestic product.DEF: The total value of all goods and services produced domestically by a nation during a year. It is equivalent to gross national product minus net investment incomes from foreign nations.

freeze-dried product.DEF: Foodstuff processed by quick freezing at minus 60 degrees followed by total dehydration.

domestic product.DEF: The total product of the various branches of the national economy over a fixed period, after deduction of capital consumption.

gross national product.DEF: Total output of goods and services produced by a nation's economy before capital consumption.

originating product.DEF: Product produced in a given country; where more than one country is involved in the manufacture of a product, it is an originating product of the country where processing last took place.

pharmaceutical product.DEF: qualitative and quantitative composition of a medicinal product in the pharmaceutical form, approved for administration to the patient, in line with the regulated product information

veterinary medicinal product.DEF: Any substance or combination of substances presented for treating or preventing disease in animals. According to the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE), veterinary products include vaccines, veterinary medicines such as antimicrobial agents, and diagnostic kits.

adjuvant.DEF: A substance added to a product to improve its quality or increase its effectiveness.

occupational psychology.DEF: The branch of psychology concerned with the working environment and personnel management.

professional qualifications.DEF: The particular knowledge and skills required of a person in order to carry out his job.

decontamination.DEF: The removing or the neutralisation of chemical, biological, or radiological contamination on a person, object, or area.

quorum.DEF: Minimum number of participants that must be present at a meeting to make its transactions valid.

catch quota.DEF: A proportion of the TAC (total allowable catch) allocated to the Union, a EU Member State or a third country.

electoral quota.DEF: Minimum number of votes or proportion of the votes cast required to win a seat in a system of proportional representation.

broadcasting.DEF: distribution of audio or video content to a dispersed audience

activity report.DEF: Report prepared by a delegated authorising officer outlining the performance of his duties, and financial and management information.

mass communications.DEF: Communication by means of press, radio, television etc.

ratification of an agreement.DEF: The act by which a State confirms an agreement or treaty, thus internationally binding itself to such an agreement.

vocational retraining.DEF: Training aimed at providing the skills, knowledge and aptitudes required for carrying out a task which is different from the previous one.

reinsurance.DEF: Arrangement under which an insurer passes on to other parties all or part of a risk he has assumed; this is not double insurance but a means of spreading large risks.

environmental research.DEF: Study of the environment and its modifications caused by human activities.

industrial research.DEF: Research, the aim of which is to improve methods of production or to develop new products.

recommendation.DEF: Document issued by an international organisation which does not imply any legal obligation.

recommendation (EU).DEF: Recommendations are non-mandatory acts issued by the European Commission, the Council of the European Union, or the European Central Bank which suggest a certain form of conduct to those to whom they are addressed without imposing any legal obligations.

mutual assistance scheme.DEF: Body which supplements the social security scheme by giving its members additional benefits.

redirection of production.DEF: Substitution of one agricultural activity for another.

swap arrangement.DEF: A swap is a derivatives contract for the exchange of assets (interest rates, foreign exchange, credit, equities and commodities) according to a prearranged formula.

action for failure to act.DEF: Proceeding carried out against the inaction of a Union institution, body, office or agency. If this inaction is illegal under European law, the Court shall confirm the failure to act and the institution, body, office or agency concerned must take appropriate measures.

action for failure to fulfil an obligati.DEF: Action against States who do not respect the obligations imposed on them by the treaties.

waste recycling.DEF: The reprocessing of the waste materials originating during a production process to obtain similar or other products than the original material.

rediscounting.DEF: Operation in which a central bank discounts a bill presented by another bank which has already discounted it.

summary procedure.DEF: An urgent court hearing to stop a situation which is against the law.

referendum.DEF: Vote by the general community to accept or reject a measure proposed by the government.

documentary credit.DEF: Credit opened with a bank to guarantee payment for goods on presentation of certain documents.

agrarian reform.DEF: Reform covering all aspects of agrarian institutions, i.e. land reform, production structures, administration of rural areas etc.

farm development plan.DEF: Modernisation programme comprising a selective system of incentives for farms having an improvement plan.

guarantee threshold.DEF: Prices are no longer guaranteed if production exceeds a certain predetermined level.

land reform.DEF: Complete reform of the land system and conditions of agricultural production in order to eliminate obstacles to economic and social development.

refugee.DEF: Someone who is unable or unwilling to return to their country of origin owing to a well-founded fear of being persecuted for reasons of race, religion, nationality, membership of a particular social group, or political opinion.

forestry group.DEF: Civil-law association formed for the purpose of preventing the break-up of private forestry holdings.

refusal to sell.DEF: The refusal of a producer or distributor to sell goods or services.

fishing licence.DEF: Document affixed to a fishing vessel flying the flag of a Member State or granted to a vessel flying the flag of a third country authorised to fish in the EU waters. It contains information concerning the identification, technical characteristics and fitting out of the vessel.

partly nationalised undertaking.DEF: Company competing in the production of goods and services, the object of which activity is to maintain or create employment.

commercial media.DEF: Media which derive part of their income from advertising.

video conference.DEF: Conference in which the speakers are situated in two or more places and connected with each other by facilities of telecommunications.

pay television.DEF: A special fee is required in order to receive programmes.

multiple office holding.DEF: One person legally holding several offices.

delegation of power.DEF: Decision of a body which is entrusted with a particular task to temporarily transfer the execution of this task to another body.

plebiscite.DEF: A direct vote by the qualified electors of a State regarding some important public issue.

privilege.DEF: The rights and immunities enjoyed by members of most legislative bodies, such as freedom of speech, freedom from arrest in civil cases during a session, etc.

consortium.DEF: Temporary grouping of independent businesses formed in order to carry out a financial or economic transaction.

economic conversion.DEF: Transformation or alteration in production rendered necessary by changes in economic conditions.

social economy.DEF: Economy of the voluntary sector covering cooperatives, associations, mutual benefit societies and foundations.

economic accounts for agriculture.DEF: Supplies all data on aspects of agricultural activity, making comparisons possible and simplifying inclusion in economic statistics.

air purifier.DEF: device which removes contaminants from the air in a room to improve indoor air quality

conciliation.DEF: procedure described in Article 314 TFEU which, in the context of the special legislative procedure in budgetary matters, provides for the convening of the Conciliation Committee in cases where the Council does not approve all amendments to a draft budget submitted by Parliament

regulation.DEF: Act of general significance issued by an authority other than parliament.

transport price.DEF: Sum demanded not only for transport from one place to another but possibly also for certain additional services.

regulation (EU).DEF: Regulations are of general application. They are mandatory in their entirety and are directly applicable in all Member States.

erosion.DEF: The general process whereby the materials of Earth's crust are loosened, dissolved, or worn away by natural agents, but usually excludes mass wasting such as landslide.

export levy.DEF: Levy applied when the internal prices are lower than world prices in order to prevent shortages.

import levy.DEF: A duty imposed on imports of products so as to bring prices to a level equal to those on the domestic market.

Nimexe.DEF: Nomenclature of Goods for the External Trade Statistics of the Community and Statistics of Trade between Member States.

countertrade.DEF: Form of international trade aimed at eliminating or reducing the transfer of currencies. Re-introduces bartering, counter-buying, and re-purchasing agreements.

reflation.DEF: Policy designed to give new impetus to economic activity which is in a state of decline or stagnation.

bilateral relations.DEF: Organisation of international trade based on direct agreements between two states.

merchandising.DEF: The various techniques used to render a product or a service as attractive as possible to the consumer.

theory of marketing.DEF: The various measures taken to detect, forecast or stimulate the needs of consumers and subsequently adapt production and marketing.

affiliated retailing.DEF: Distribution system in which retailers, while remaining independent businesses, join groups or associations which pool the purchasing of goods and provide affiliates with certain other services.

wholesale trading centre.DEF: Centralised market which simplifies distribution channels by reducing the number of middlemen between producers and consumers.

inter-industrial relations.DEF: Flow of goods and services between different industries.

transfer pricing.DEF: Method used by companies to export capital by charging their subsidiaries greatly increased prices for products supplied by the parent company.

very short-term financing.DEF: Credit facilities arranged between the central banks to allow interventions in Community currencies.

multilateral relations.DEF: Organisation of relations based on mechanisms which promote relations between each country and all its partners.

co-insurance.DEF: Joint coverage of a large risk by a number of insurers under a single contract, each insurer being liable for a portion of any claims.

financing of the EU budget.DEF: Financial resources or incomes of the European Union.

commemorative document.DEF: complimentary or memorial publication issued in honour of a person or an organization, usually on the occasion of an anniversary celebration

bracket rate.DEF: Scale comprising of minimum and maximum limits within which prices can vary.

support tariff.DEF: Tariff which favours national carriers (prohibited without the authorisation of the Commission).

cybernetics.DEF: Study of systems of communications and control in machines and living beings.

single market.DEF: Refers to the EU as one territory without any internal borders or other regulatory obstacles to the free movement of goods and services as defined by the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union.

parental authority.DEF: Power granted by law to a father and mother over the person or property of their child, who is not of full age and capacity.

population ageing.DEF: Increase in the proportion of older persons in the total population.

job mobility.DEF: Ability of an individual to change his/her position or rank within a profession or to change occupation.

social budget.DEF: Section of the budget concerned with social matters (pensions, health, education, family benefit etc.).

economic cycle.DEF: Downward and upward movement of goods and services in an economy.

proportional representation.DEF: Electoral system in which each party is represented in proportion to the numerical strength of the vote it receives.

decentralisation.DEF: Distribution of administrative powers which have been concentrated in a single centre.

economic recovery.DEF: Re-expansion of the economy after a period of recession.

farm accountancy data network.DEF: Instrument  for evaluating the income of agricultural holdings and the impacts of the Common Agricultural Policy, established on the basis of information from farm accounts, representing the various types of farming within the European Union.

reserves.DEF: Amounts set aside by a business in anticipation of future liabilities.

provision.DEF: Sum set aside in the accounts to provide for certain anticipated losses or expenditure.

nuclear non-proliferation.DEF: International control of the transfer and utilisation of nuclear weapons.

Forum on China\u2013Africa Cooperation.DEF: platform established in 2000 by the People’s Republic of China and African countries for collective consultation and a multi-lateral cooperation mechanism between the members

nature reserve.DEF: A protected area of importance for wildlife, flora, fauna or features of geological, biological or aesthetic interest, which is reserved and managed for the conservation and restoration of the natural environment.

bilateral agreement.DEF: Agreement between two states which is only legally binding for these two states with the benefits typically not shared with other (third) countries.

signature of an agreement.DEF: Formality which acknowledges agreement on the text of a treaty but which does not normally bind the State.

resolution.DEF: Document issued by an international organisation, the legal implication of which may vary.

European convention.DEF: Combine with the related subject of the Council of Europe's convention.

relations between the two German States.DEF: Political and economic relations between East and West Germany.

code of conduct.DEF: A text which is binding on States or private persons and lays down international standards simplifying the drafting and application of national policies, laws and regulations in specific fields.

international sanctions.DEF: Measures taken against a State which has violated international law.

decision (EU).DEF: Decisions are binding in their entirety. Decisions which specify those to whom they are addressed are binding only on them (Article 288 TFEU).

legal cooperation.DEF: Cooperation between States aimed at drafting joint regulations or harmonising legislation.

Armenian question.DEF: Refers to Europe's involvement with the Armenian subjects of the Ottoman Empire, beginning with the Russo-Turkish War of 1877–78.

Kurdistan question.DEF: Conflict between Turkey and Kurdish insurgent groups, which have demanded separation from Turkey to create an independent Kurdistan.

international responsibility.DEF: International obligation to repair damages caused to foreigners as a result of acts contrary to international law.

arms control.DEF: According to NATO, arms control refers to mutually agreed-upon restraints or controls (usually between states) on the research, manufacture, or the levels of and/or locales of deployment of troops and weapons systems.

peace zone.DEF: Area free from nuclear arms or foreign military installations.

reintegration into working life.DEF: Return to the job market after a long period of absence due to maternity leave, children's education, military service, imprisonment, etc.

job sharing.DEF: System in which an employee agrees to work fewer hours, resulting in a reduction of salary, in order to permit an unemployed person to work.

national.DEF: person having a legal bond with a state

temporary employment.DEF: Work which requires the recruitment of a person for a fixed length of time.

updating of skills.DEF: Training provided for those workers no longer familiar with technical progress in order to update their skills.

water resources.DEF: Refer to the water available for use in a territory and include surface waters (in other words, coastal bays, lakes, rivers and streams) and groundwater.

expatriate worker.DEF: Term solely concerning workers posted abroad in accordance with company policy.

entrepreneur.DEF: One who organises, owns and manages a business, assuming the risks involved.

teleworking.DEF: Work carried out at a distance using telecommunication services or computers.

own resources.DEF: The tax revenue allocated to the European Union to finance its expenditure, which must not exceed the EU GNI ceiling. Own resources comprise agricultural duties, customs duties, a VAT resource, sugar and isoglucose levies, GNI contributions and 'other revenue' e.g.  tax and deductions from EU staff remuneration.

export refund.DEF: Subsidy, under the common agricultural policy, on exports of agricultural produce to provide producers with guaranteed prices.

professional association.DEF: Associations of certain professions which are not included in the trade union movement.

trade union.DEF: An association of employees, usually not limited to a single company, formed to protect or improve incomes and working conditions by collective bargaining with employers or employer organisations.

devolution.DEF: System in which the administration of a region is executed by local authorities subject to a central authority.

transit.DEF: Act of passing through a country when the points of arrival and departure are situated outside this country.

technology park.DEF: Physical place supporting university-industry and government collaboration that incorporates research activities, centers of higher education and advanced industries.

clean technology.DEF: refers to the development of new technologies which aim to conserve, monitor or reduce the negative impact of technology on the environment and the consumption of resources

decree.DEF: Enforceable decision taken by a legislative body.

EU trade mark.DEF: European Union Trademark recognised and protected  in all the  Member States of the EU and registered with the European Union Intellectual Property Office (EUIPO).

experiment on humans.DEF: The use of humans as investigational subjects.

national income.DEF: The aggregate earnings of labour and property which arise from the current production of goods and services by the nation's economy.

deflation.DEF: A decline in the general price level, e.g. in the consumer price index.

citizen.DEF: legally recognised person who is affiliated to an area, usually a state or a territory, and who is entitled to certain protection, rights and privileges and subject to certain obligations

ADN agreement.DEF: European agreement relating to the international transportation of dangerous goods by inland shipping.

African Continental Free Trade Area.DEF: free trade area established by the African Continental Free Trade Agreement which aims at accelerating intra-African trade and boosting Africa’s trading position in the global market

AfCFTA countries.DEF: countries that are part of the African Continental Free Trade Area

hydroelectric development.DEF: The total construction work involved in setting up a hydroelectric plant.

bio-industry.DEF: Branch of industry using biotechnology at an industrial and commercial level.

biotechnology.DEF: Branch of technology aimed at cultivating micro-organisms, animal and vegetable cells and their components.

medicinal product.DEF: A substance or combination of substances that is intended to treat, prevent or diagnose a disease, or to restore, correct or modify physiological functions by exerting a pharmacological, immunological or metabolic action.

Saint Martin.DEF: French overseas collectivity, with the special denomination ‘Collectivity of Saint Martin’.

wage earner.DEF: A person who works for a public or private employer and receives wages, salaries, room and board or other compensation for his/her efforts.

administrative sanction.DEF: Generally, any formal official imposition of penalty or fine; destruction, taking, seizure, or withholding of property; assessment of damages, reimbursement, restitution, compensation, costs, charges or fees; requirement, revocation or suspension of license; and taking other compulsory or restrictive action by organization, agency or its representative.

private limited company.DEF: Company with share capital and with legal personality possessing separate assets which alone serve to cover its debts.

gender equality.DEF: Result of the absence of discrimination on the basis of a person’s sex in opportunities and the allocation of resources or benefits or in access to services.

right to development.DEF: Every person has the right to participate in economic, social, cultural and political development, and to contribute to it and benefit from it. Human rights and basic freedoms are an integral part of such development.

child protection.DEF: Various measures whose purpose is to improve conditions for children in society.

non-EU national.DEF: any person who is not a citizen of the European Union, thus not enjoying right of free movement

easement.DEF: Right attached to one piece of land entitling the owner thereof to some right over adjacent land but not to take any part or produce thereof.

legal aid.DEF: Assistance granted to persons in need to enable them to exercise their legal rights.

rights of the defence.DEF: all the prerogatives guaranteed to the subjects of legal proceeding, to enable them to assert their interests and to effectively ensure their defence guaranteed rights for anyone who has been charged

preliminary ruling procedure.DEF: Procedure exercised before the Court of Justice of the European Union that enables national courts of the EU countries to question the Court of Justice on the interpretation or validity of EU law.

international law - national law.DEF: Effects of international law, particularly of treaties, on the national law of a State.

public economic law.DEF: The law applied to economic cases brought by public persons.

quaternary sector.DEF: Sector of the economy regarding intellectual services, education, consultancy, information, research.

secondary legislation.DEF: All legislative acts adopted by the European institutions in accordance with the Treaties.

implementing Regulation.DEF: Regulation adopted by the Commission or by the Council under the implementing powers conferred upon them by a legislative act (Article 291 TFEU).

job security.DEF: A work contract which guarantees a long period of employment.

Protocol (EU).DEF: Protocol on the privileges and immunities of the European Union.

nuclear safety.DEF: Prevention of accidents from undue radiation hazards.

European Social Fund.DEF: Set up under the Treaty of Rome to improve employment chances for workers in the internal market and contribute to the raising of living standards.

European Union.DEF: Objective of a reform project of the treaties for the creation of a European Union.

environmental risk prevention.DEF: Applies to the prevention of environmental risks.

industrial hazard.DEF: Potential and more-or-less predictable danger which can arise at an industrial site, with immediate serious consequences for the adjacent population, property or environment.

irradiation.DEF: Method of preserving foodstuffs by the use of rays.

disarmament.DEF: According to NATO, disarmament refers to the act of eliminating or abolishing weapons (particularly offensive arms) either unilaterally (in the hope that one’s example will be followed) or reciprocally.

genetic engineering.DEF: Deliberate production of new genes by substituting or adding a new genetic component.

promulgation of a law.DEF: Official publication of a new law, thereby putting it into effect.

natural disaster.DEF: Act of nature of such magnitude as to create a catastrophic situation in which the day-to-day patterns of life are suddenly disrupted and people are plunged into helplessness and suffering, and, as a result, need food, clothing, shelter, medical and nursing care and other necessities of life, and protection against unfavourable environmental factors and conditions.

most favoured nation.DEF: Clause appearing in certain bilateral agreements whereby the contracting States agree to extend to their reciprocal trade the customs advantages which they would grant to another party.

subsidiary budget.DEF: Budgets annexed to the general budget for certain public bodies (e.g. Post Office) which are not independent legal entities but have a degree of financial autonomy.

civil disobedience.DEF: Refusal to obey laws considered as unjust by means of non-violent protest.

professional partnership.DEF: Partnership established for the exercise of certain liberal professions.

mixed-ownership company.DEF: Company owned partly by the government or a public body and partly by private-sector investors.

investment company.DEF: An organisation formed for the purpose of pooling investors' funds to invest in a range of securities.

consumer society.DEF: A type of society where growth in production results in a proliferation of consumer goods and consequently in the creation of new needs and desires.

undisclosed partnership.DEF: Unregistered company without corporate or legal personality which is not required to make itself public and which may remain secret.

sample survey.DEF: Study of a sample representative of a population so as to determine characteristics.

self-determination.DEF: The right of a nation or people to determine its own form of government without influence from outside.

external debt.DEF: Public or private debt to foreign creditors.

public debt.DEF: Liabilities of central government and other public bodies to individual creditors.

budgetary specification.DEF: Principle under which appropriations must be used for the specific purpose laid down in the budget.

economic stabilisation.DEF: return to a state of economic stability after a period of fluctuation, which may apply to a market or the economy as a whole

official statistics.DEF: Statistics describing phenomena of public interest to policy makers, the economic agents and the public at large. They are developed, produced and disseminated by the statistical authorities in compliance with the provisions of the Union and national law and the European statistics Code of Practice / National Codes of Practice.

political status.DEF: Concerns countries or regions whose status is controversial.

reshoring.DEF: transfer of a business operation, especially manufacturing, back to its country of origin

minimum stock.DEF: Lowest level which stocks of any item should be allowed to reach in the course of normal business.

buffer stock.DEF: Stocks of commodities held to reduce fluctuations in world commodity prices.

dangerous substance.DEF: A substance or a mixture fulfilling the criteria's relating to physical, health or environmental hazards as defined by the Regulation (EC) No 1272/2008 (regulation on the Classification, Labelling and Packaging of substances and mixtures).

votes cast.DEF: Votes validly cast excluding blank and invalid ballot papers.

Kyoto Protocol.DEF: The Kyoto Protocol is an international agreement linked to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change. It sets binding targets for 37 industrialized countries and the European Union for reducing greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions. The major distinction between the Protocol and the Convention is that while the Convention encouraged industrialised countries to stabilize GHG emissions, the Protocol commits them to do so.

adaptation to climate change.DEF: Policies and measures to decrease the vulnerability of natural and human systems against actual or expected climate change effects.

emission trading.DEF: A market-based mechanism under the Kyoto Protocol that allows countries reducing greenhouse gas emissions below what is required to use or trade the excess reductions to offset emissions at another source inside or outside the country.

clean development mechanism.DEF: A mechanism under the Kyoto Protocol through which developed countries may finance greenhouse-gas emission reduction or removal projects in developing countries, and receive carbon credits - Certified Emission Reductions, CER - for doing so which they may apply towards meeting mandatory limits on their own emissions

joint implementation.DEF: A market-based implementation mechanism under the Kyoto Protocol, allowing countries or companies from these countries to implement projects jointly that limit or reduce emissions or enhance sinks, and to share the Emissions Reduction Units (ERU)

emission allowance.DEF: The portion of total allowable emissions assigned to a country or group of countries within a framework of maximum total emissions.

carbon capture and storage.DEF: A process consisting of separation of CO2 from industrial and energy-related sources, transport to a storage location, and long-term isolation from the atmosphere.

human cloning.DEF: Human reproductive cloning with the goal of bringing an embryo to term and producing a live individual, or therapeutic cloning to produce embryonic stem cells for use in medical and scientific research and medical treatments.

EU law - international law.DEF: Influence of the European Union law on the international law and vice versa.

silviculture.DEF: The branch of forestry that is concerned with the cultivation of trees.

geopolitics.DEF: The study of geographical influences on countries' domestic and foreign policies.

open source software.DEF: Software that can be freely used, changed, and shared (in modified or unmodified form) by anyone.

management information system.DEF: System in which defined data are collected, processed and communicated to assist those responsible for the use of resources.

accounting system.DEF: The set of accounting procedures, internal mechanisms of control, books of account, and plan and chart of accounts that are used for administering, recording, and reporting on financial transactions.

European electoral system.DEF: The uniform electoral procedure laid down in the EU treaties for the direct election of members to the European Parliament by universal suffrage.

European accounting system.DEF: Internationally compatible EU accounting framework for a systematic and detailed description of an economy.

European Monetary System.DEF: The European Monetary System, abbreviated as EMS, was an exchange rate regime set up in 1979 (and which ended in 1999) to foster closer monetary policy co-operation between the central banks of the Member States of the European Economic Community (EEC). The objective of the EMS was to promote monetary stability in Europe. The European Monetary System was built on the concept of stable but adjustable exchange rates defined according to the newly created European currency unit (ECU) – a currency basket based on a weighted average of EMS currencies. Within the EMS, currency fluctuations were controlled through the Exchange Rate Mechanism (ERM).

European Neighbourhood and Partnership I.DEF: Financial instrument for European neighbourhood policy (ENP) which is addressed to ENP partner countries including Russia and offers co-funding for promoting good governance and equitable social and economic development.

Common Frame of Reference.DEF: Long-term project, which aims at providing the European Legislators with a "toolbox" or a handbook to be used for the revision of existing and the preparation of new legislation in the area of contract law. This toolbox could contain fundamental principles of contract law, definitions of key concepts and model provisions.

digital literacy.DEF: Ability to use digital technologies effectively and to understand the implications of the operations performed.

transportation tariff.DEF: Transport price fixed in advance according to a systematic table.

self-sufficiency rate.DEF: Relationship between the production and consumption of a product within a given area.

central rate.DEF: The official exchange rate of ERM II member currencies vis-à-vis the euro, around which the ERM II fluctuation margins are defined.

representative rate.DEF: Special rate for conversion between the ECU and a national currency for the purposes of farm prices, deviating from the normal exchange rate.

President of the European Council.DEF: public official presiding over and driving forward the work of the European Council, while also ensuring the external representation of the European Union on issues concerning its common foreign and security policy

stamp duty.DEF: Tax on legal documents etc., the payment of which is certified by the attaching or impressing of official stamps.

ordinary legislative procedure.DEF: Normal procedure for adopting EU legislative acts, whereby the European Parliament and the Council, acting jointly, adopt a regulation, directive or decision on a proposal from the Commission.

special legislative procedure.DEF: In the specific cases provided for in the Treaties, adoption of a regulation, directive or decision by the European Parliament with the participation of the Council or by the Council with the participation of the European Parliament.

charge having equivalent effect.DEF: Having an effect equivalent to that of customs duties.

legislative act (EU).DEF: Legal acts adopted by an ordinary or special legislative procedure.

non-legislative act (EU).DEF: Legal acts adopted outside a legislative procedure.

implementing decision.DEF: Decision adopted by the Commission or by the Council under the implementing powers conferred upon them by a legislative act (Article 291 TFEU).

business tax.DEF: Tax on the income or capital of corporations or analogous legal entities.

delegated decision.DEF: Delegated acts supplement or modify certain non-essential provisions of a legislative act. Such acts are adopted by the Commission, under the supervision of the legislator – the European Parliament and/or the Council of the European Union – which may withdraw its delegation at any time (Article 290 TFEU).

implementing directive.DEF: Directive adopted by the Commission or by the Council under the implementing powers conferred upon them by a legislative act (Article 291 TFEU).

delegated directive.DEF: Delegated acts supplement or modify certain non-essential provisions of a legislative act. Such acts are adopted by the Commission, under the supervision of the legislator – the European Parliament and/or the Council of the European Union – which may withdraw its delegation at any time (Article 290 TFEU).

delegated regulation.DEF: Delegated acts supplement or modify certain non-essential provisions of a legislative act. Such acts are adopted by the Commission, under the supervision of the legislator – the European Parliament and/or the Council of the European Union – which may withdraw its delegation at any time (Article 290 TFEU).

executive agency.DEF: These agencies are legal entities established in accordance with Council Regulation (EC) No 58/2003 (OJ L 11, 16.1.2003) with a view to being entrusted with certain tasks relating to the management of one or more European Union programmes. They are set up for a fixed period.

food technology.DEF: Operations, equipment and measures involved in the processing of food.

cultural transmission.DEF: Dissemination and promotion of cultural diversity at local and national level.

intermediate technology.DEF: Technology which can improve the productivity of traditional methods without requiring the capital or educational training necessary for advanced technology.

telecommunications.DEF: The transmission, broadcasting or reception of signals, sounds, messages or information of any nature by electric means, e.g. wire, radio or other electromagnetic systems.

remote sensing.DEF: All techniques used to determine the physical and biological features of objects by measures carried out at a distance without material contact with the object concerned.

cable distribution.DEF: System using a network of cables to broadcast audio or visual programmes to a large number of users.

telematics.DEF: All services, other than the normal telephonic and telegraphic services, which use teleinformatic techniques and which can be received by users of a telecommunications network.

cultural tourism.DEF: Cultural tourism is the subset of tourism which concerns the culture of a particular country or region, specifically the lifestyle of the people in the geographical areas in question, their history, art, architecture, religion(s) and other elements which have helped shape their way of life.

terms of trade.DEF: A measure of a country's trading prospects based on the ratio of an index of export prices to an index of import prices.

consent procedure.DEF: In certain legislative areas, the European Parliament is requested to give its consent, as a special legislative procedure under Article 289(2) of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU). The consent procedure gives Parliament the right of veto. Parliament’s role is thus to approve or reject the legislative proposal without further amendments and the Council cannot overrule Parliament’s opinion. Consent is also required as a non-legislative procedure when the Council is adopting certain international agreements.

European Central Bank opinion.DEF: The European Central Bank may submit opinions concerning matters within its competence to the relevant EU institutions, bodies or agencies or national authorities.

renewable fuel.DEF: fuel produced from renewable energy sources

board of management.DEF: Committee of managers responsible for managing the company and answerable to the board.

Council configuration.DEF: The Council meets – according to the subject being discussed – in different "configurations", which are attended by the Ministers from the Member States and the European Commissioners responsible for the areas concerned. Since the entry into force of the Treaty of Lisbon on 1 December 2009, there have been ten configurations.

Presidency trio.DEF: The EU’s 28 Member States take it in turn to chair the Council for a period of six months each. In the interest of continuity of Council business, the six-monthly successive presidencies work together closely in groups of three. These three-Presidency teams draw up a joint programme of Council work over an 18-month period.

European Union Agency for Asylum.DEF: European Union Agency for Asylum (successor of the European Asylum Support Office, EASO) supports the implementation of the Common European Asylum System

directive.DEF: Order from a Head of State or Government.

European Joint Undertaking.DEF: Association of firms or individuals formed to undertake a specific business project. Under the EU competition rules, joint ventures are undertakings jointly controlled by two or more other undertakings. In practice, joint ventures encompass a broad range of operations, from merger-type operations to cooperation in relation to particular activities, such as research and development, production or distribution.

technology transfer.DEF: The transfer from one country to another of the knowledge, manufacturing techniques and equipment necessary for the production of goods.

Union transit.DEF: Customs transit procedure which applies within the European Union.

customs transit.DEF: Arrangements for moving goods through a territory without payment of customs duties.

combined transport.DEF: The dispatch of goods using several means of transport, the greatest distance possible being covered by rail, inland waterway or sea, and the shortest by road.

Northern Mariana Islands.DEF: Commonwealth in political union with the USA.

inland waterway transport.DEF: type of transport using navigable waterways like rivers, canals, lakes, and other inland bodies of water

inland transport.DEF: Transport movement where the points of arrival and departure are situated within the territory of the same State.

European fisheries fund.DEF: Provided funding to the fishing industry and coastal communities to help them adapt to changing conditions in the sector and become economically resilient and ecologically sustainable for the period 2007-2013.

transport under customs control.DEF: Permission to cross customs territory or to convey imports to a customs warehouse or customs clearing centre without fulfilling customs formalities at the border.

part-time employment.DEF: Employment with monthly working hours which are shorter than those normally worked by full-time employees.

moonlighting.DEF: The holding of an employment over and above the basic job, usually in breach of rules laid down by law.

clandestine worker.DEF: Worker who carries out a remunerated activity in violation of the law.

customs union.DEF: States which have established among themselves a single customs area with common external customs regulations and tariffs.

preferential agreement.DEF: An EU trade agreement containing tariff provisions more favourable than those regulated by the WTO.

town planning.DEF: Science and policies concerning the construction and organisation of towns.

land use.DEF: Socioeconomic use of land (e.g. agriculture, forestry, recreation or residential use).

market capitalisation.DEF: Total value at current market prices of all the issued shares of a company or of the shares of all the companies listed on a market.

direct selling.DEF: Sales method where producers or manufacturers sell their products direct to private individuals without going through an intermediary (retailer or wholesale).

broadcast videography.DEF: Videography where messages are broadcast by a television network.

interactive videotex.DEF: Videography where a telecommunications network transmits the requests of users and the messages received in reply.

satellite town.DEF: Town which is politically and economically dependent on another town.

vote on a text as a whole.DEF: procedure in France whereby the government can force the Assembly to vote on the whole text under discussion, allowing only those amendments proposed or accepted by itself

preferential voting.DEF: Form of voting in which candidates are numbered in order of preference by the voter.

building performance.DEF: attribute of a building that expresses how well that building carries out its functions

package travel.DEF: A combination of at least two different types of travel services for the purpose of the same trip or holiday where the travel services are advertised as a package, are booked within the same booking process or where they are offered or charged at a total or inclusive price.

agricultural advisory services.DEF: Dissemination to farmers of technical, financial and economic knowledge.

free-trade area.DEF: States which have eliminated customs duties among themselves and established on their territories an area within which goods move freely.

fishing area.DEF: The name of the fishing area or division listed under the FAO Fishing Areas.

exclusive economic zone.DEF: Zone extending beyond the territorial waters up to a distance of 200 miles from the coast.

free zone.DEF: Section of territory where customs duties are not applicable.

tariff zone.DEF: Geographical area inside of which there is a uniform transport price.

land bank.DEF: Body established with a view to acquiring land or farms for sale which are intended to be re-assigned after possible development.

manpower needs.DEF: General demand for labour or demand in particular industries, sectors or economies.

geoengineering.DEF: deliberate large-scale intervention in the Earth’s natural systems

energy market.DEF: The trade or traffic of energy sources treated as a commodity (such as fossil fuel, electricity, or solar radiation).

social audit.DEF: The systematic evaluation of an organisation's social impact in relation to standards and expectations.

bioconversion.DEF: Direct or indirect transformation of solar energy by living beings.

bioenergy.DEF: All forms of energy originating from the transformation of biomasses.

biogas.DEF: Gaseous substance resulting from the decomposition of organic matter.

biomass.DEF: All organic matter which forms living beings, animal or vegetable.

bipolarisation.DEF: Situation in certain countries where the political scene is dominated by the struggle for power between two political movements.

treasury bill.DEF: An exchequer bill payable at short notice.

commodities exchange.DEF: Market where the bulk sale and purchase of commodities (wool, coffee, cocoa) take place, often for future delivery.

ECSC operating budget.DEF: Budget for ECSC activities, separate from the general budget of the European Communities.

inclusion in the budget.DEF: Incorporation into the budget of particular items of revenue and expenditure.

shadow cabinet.DEF: Group of leaders of the Opposition, each assigned to watch a major government department so as to challenge government policy in that field. If government changes, members may be appointed to those departments they have shadowed.

maritime cabotage.DEF: Merchant shipping between neighbouring ports or EU ports.

marketing year.DEF: Annual reference period for the fixing of farm prices.

consultation procedure.DEF: Under Article 289 of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU), consultation is a special legislative procedure, whereby Parliament is asked for its opinion on proposed legislation before the Council adopts it.

EP delegation.DEF: Official groups of Members of the European Parliament that maintain and deepen relations with the parliaments of non-EU countries, regions and organisations.

ESC opinion.DEF: The European Economic and Social Committee issues technical opinions on economic and social matters. It delivers mandatory opinions where the Treaty so provides. It may also be consulted whenever Parliament, the Commission or the Council deems it necessary, even when this is not provided for by the Treaty. Opinions are used to guide these institutions in their legislative activity and are not binding.

Structural Funds.DEF: Financial instruments used by the European Commission to promote the economic and social cohesion of the European Union.

contiguous zone.DEF: Strip of water extending beyond the territorial waters at a distance of less than 24 miles from the coast.

venture capital.DEF: A subset of a private equity that refers to equity investments made for the launch, early development (seed and start-up), or expansion of a business.

bio-ethics.DEF: Ethical aspects of techniques involving human intervention in biological processes.

Eurydice.DEF: Information network on education in Europe.

Teletex.DEF: Text transmission service enabling the various functions of text processing to be carried out remotely.

anti-dumping duty.DEF: Countervailing duty imposed on imports to discourage dumping.

right to work.DEF: Every person has the right to work and to exercise a profession freely chosen or accepted.

quality standard.DEF: sets of good management practices, methods, systems, requirements, and/or specifications established by industry advisory groups to help manufacturers achieve and demonstrate consistent production and product quality

technical standard.DEF: established norm or requirement for a repeatable technical task which is applied to a common and repeated use of rules, conditions, guidelines or characteristics for products or related processes and production methods, and related management systems practices

authorised catch.DEF: Catch limits (expressed in tonnes or numbers) that are set annually for most commercial fish stocks (every two years for deep-sea stocks) and shared between EU countries in the form of national quotas.

EU act.DEF: EU legal acts are legislative or non-legislative acts adopted by the European institutions (Article 288 TFEU).

citizenship.DEF: relationship between a natural person and an area, usually a state or territory, which confers on that person full political, civil and social rights

cartel.DEF: Association of independent companies with similar activities, formed for the purpose of limiting or eliminating competition in a particular market.

cash flow.DEF: A company's gross cash flow is its net profit before charging depreciation. The net cash flow consists of retained profits plus depreciation.

electoral deposit.DEF: Sum which a candidate has to deposit at an election.

ionising radiation.DEF: Energy transferred in the form of particles or electromagnetic waves of a wavelength of 100 nanometres or less capable of producing ions directly or indirectly.

nuclear medicine.DEF: The field of medicine in which radio nuclides are used for diagnosis or therapy.

performance drugs.DEF: Any substance used for the abnormal enhancement of an individual's physical or mental performance.

impact of information technology.DEF: To be used for the positive and negative impacts of using information technology in life, for example with regards to employment, privacy, and access to services.

radiobiology.DEF: Study of the effects of radiation on living tissue or organisms.

cellulose.DEF: A chemical compound occurring naturally in fibrous products such as cotton and kapok, and used in the manufacture of paper, rayon, cellophane, etc.

chaptalisation.DEF: Method of adding sugar to wine.

ATP Agreement.DEF: Agreement on the international carriage of perishable foodstuffs and on the special equipment to be used for such carriage.

trade agreement (EU).DEF: Agreement between EU and one or more countries to establish a free trade area where commerce in goods and services can be conducted across their common borders, without tariffs or hindrances.

Schengen Agreement.DEF: Agreement aimed at the gradual abolition of controls on persons at the internal frontiers of the EU.

interim agreement (EU).DEF: Provisional application of a European Union agreement.

Community acquis.DEF: Common foundation of rights and obligations which binds together the Member States of the European Union.

associated action for damages.DEF: Action brought by a victim of crime in association with criminal proceedings.

public prosecution.DEF: Action brought before a criminal court by the public prosecutor's department with a view to passing an appropriate sentence on the perpetrator of a crime.

EU activity.DEF: The EU’s overall political strategy is developed jointly by the European Council, the European Council President and the President of the Commission. The Commission proposes policies and laws to implement that strategy.

adaptation of financial perspectives.DEF: Comprises the annual technical adjustments made by the Commission and the adjustments connected to the implementing conditions.

accession to an agreement.DEF: Act by which a State or international organisation declares its readiness to be bound by an agreement already concluded by other parties.

fishing rights.DEF: System of fisheries management under which access to fishing grounds is governed by participatory rights that comprise not only the entitlement to catch fish but also specifications regarding the following aspects: how fishing may be conducted (e.g. type of vessel and engine), when and where it may be carried out and the size of authorised catches.

legal language.DEF: specialised language used in the legal profession, documents and official proceedings, often characterised as a formal, precise and often complex form of communication designed to convey specific meanings and intentions in a clear and unambiguous manner

biodiversity.DEF: Biological diversity within and across species, and within terrestrial or aquatic ecosystems.

biotope.DEF: A biotope is a homogeneous area of similar ecology which constitutes the habitat of a specific animal and vegetable community.

air cabotage.DEF: Commercial flights operated between two places in one country by another country's airline.

quality control circle.DEF: A group of workers, performing similar work and trained to identify and solve problems, who volunteer to make recommendations relating to the improvement of productivity, quality, work morale, etc. in an undertaking.

codification of EU law.DEF: Codification is the process of bringing together a legislative act and all its amendments in a single new act. The new act passes through the full legislative process and replaces the acts being codified.

economic and social cohesion.DEF: Objective implemented through the cohesion policy of the EU to achieve balanced socio-economic development throughout the EU Member States.

financial accounting.DEF: The annual financial statements shall constitute a composite whole and shall for all undertakings comprise, as a minimum, the balance sheet, the profit and loss account and the notes to the financial statements.

management committee (EU).DEF: Committee responsible for issuing opinions on the implementing measures proposed by the Commission, operating in accordance with the management procedure laid down in Article 4 of the Comitology Decision.

regulatory committee (EU).DEF: Committee responsible for issuing opinions on the implementation measures proposed by the Commission, operating in accordance with the regulatory procedure laid down in Article 5 of the Comitology Decision.

comitology.DEF: The rules laid down in Regulation (EU) No 182/2011 defining how the Commission exercises the implementing powers conferred on it by the legislative authority (the European Parliament and the Council), with the help of committees which it chairs, comprising representatives of the Member States.

intergovernmental conference (EU).DEF: Negotiations held between the governments of the Member States with a view to amending the Treaties.

leave for political activities.DEF: Leave granted to take part in a political campaign or to carry out the duties of an elected representative.

border control.DEF: activity carried out at a border in response exclusively to an intention to cross or the act of crossing that border, regardless of any other consideration, consisting of border checks and border surveillance

environmental cooperation.DEF: Cooperation in the field of environmental protection.

COSAC.DEF: A conference bringing together members of the committees of the national parliaments of the European Union Member States dealing with European affairs and representatives of the European Parliament.

sustainable development.DEF: Development which allows present needs to be satisfied without compromising the capacity of future generations to satisfy their needs too.

national accounts.DEF: System of accounting used to compile national accounts.

international human rights law.DEF: International human rights law lays down obligations by which States are bound to respect, to protect and to fulfil human rights.

Cohesion Fund.DEF: A financial instrument intended to reduce the gap in the economic performances of the Member States, thereby promoting economic and monetary union.

image.DEF: The image which the general public has of an institution, person or service.

EU initiative.DEF: An action undertaken by the EU to resolve problems connected with the implementation of EU policies on a regional scale, or to resolve those problems which are common to certain categories of region.

organic farming.DEF: A system of agricultural production that avoids or minimises the use of chemicals.

economic instrument for the environment.DEF: An instrument which influences the costs and advantages of the various options available to economic agents and which aims at changing the latter's attitudes towards the environment.

systems interconnection.DEF: ability of systems to exchange and make use of information in a straightforward and useful way; this is enhanced by the use of standards in communication and data format

EC conformity marking.DEF: The CE marking indicates a product’s compliance with EU legislation and so enables the free movement of products within the European market.

material of animal origin.DEF: Materials of animal origin that people do not consume.

over-the-counter drug.DEF: Medicinal product not subject to medical prescription.

national implementing measure.DEF: This is one or more texts adopted officially by a Member State incorporating the provisions of a directive into its national law.

Combined Nomenclature.DEF: Tariff and statistical nomenclature applied to the external trade of the Europan Union and to the trade between Member States.
